---
alwaysApply: true
---

Never import items from the following modules directly:

- `mcc_syntax::ast::*`
- `mcc::codegen::asm::*`
- `mcc:lowering::tacky::*`
- `mcc::typechecking::hir::*`

Instead, import the module and refer to its items using `module::TypeName`.

For example,

```rs
// GOOD
use mcc::typechecking::hir;
fn do_stuff(tu: hir::TranslationUnit) {}

// BAD
use mcc::typechecking::hir::TranslationUnit;
fn do_stuff(tu: TranslationUnit) {}
```

The rationale for this is that the codebase contains several different sets of intermediate representations, many of which include types with the same name but different semantics. For example, `ast::TranslationUnit` represents a parsed concrete syntax tree, possibly including errors and invalid code, whereas a `hir::TranslationUnit` contains the fully resolved items in the translation unit. By qualifying all uses of the names with their module, we avoid confusion or ambiguity.
